Reasoning: The paper deals with problems related to discrete memoryless channels and their ordering, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). The use of majorization-based conditions and convex optimization suggests a focus on mathematical analysis and optimization (cs.ITP). The mention of sparsity and iterative algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the determination of channel inclusion, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the use of permutation of input and output symbols suggests a possible connection to combinatorics and discrete structures (cs.DS).
